Prepare Near East rice according to package directions, except omit butter or olive oil. In a small bowl, mix oil, vinegar, garlic and thyme together. Set aside. While rice cooks, place already cut vegetables in a medium baking pan and drizzle vegetables with oil mixture. Bake at 400 degrees F. for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Stir vegetables into rice mixture. Garnish with fresh thyme sprig, if desired.